# 11.7 Hypothesis-Based Debugging

Instead of randomly modifying code,

the project adopted hypothesis-driven debugging.

Each hypothesis had to be proven or disproven.

Example

Hypothesis

```
Gemini API is broken.
```

Experiment

Run Gemini only.

Result

```
False
```

Gemini worked correctly.

Therefore,

Gemini was eliminated as a suspect.

---

# 11.8 Debugging Phase 1 — Gemini

Objective

Verify

- API Key
- Gemini Model
- ADK

Result

Initially,

API keys had to be corrected.

The deprecated model

```
gemini-2.0-flash
```

was replaced with

```
gemini-2.5-flash
```

After these corrections,

Gemini executed successfully.

Conclusion

Gemini was functioning correctly.

---

# 11.9 Debugging Phase 2 — Scholarship MCP

Objective

Determine whether Local Python MCP servers worked.

Result

Scholarship MCP executed successfully.

Both

Local

and

Render

returned correct results.

Conclusion

STDIO communication itself was not broken.

Python-based Local MCP servers were functioning correctly.

