# 11.14 Debugging Phase 5 — Google Maps MCP

This phase uncovered multiple independent issues.

Issue 1

Incorrect API credentials.

Issue 2

Confusion between

Google AI API Key

and

Google Cloud API Key.

Issue 3

Authentication behaviour differences between

API Keys

and

Application Default Credentials (ADC).

After correcting the configuration,

Google Maps MCP executed successfully.

Conclusion

Maps authentication was independent of the Filesystem problem.

---

# 11.15 Tool Isolation Strategy

Every MCP server was isolated.

```
Gemini

↓

Scholarship

↓

Filesystem

↓

Tavily

↓

Maps
```

Only after every individual component succeeded

were they combined.

This strategy identified

Filesystem MCP

as the only remaining unstable component.

---

# 11.16 Why Removing Filesystem MCP Was Considered

At one point,

three possible solutions were evaluated.

Option A

Remove Filesystem MCP.

Option B

Replace Filesystem MCP with native Python.

Option C

Fix the runtime.

Option A

would have restored application stability,

but at the cost of losing report generation.

Option B

would have preserved functionality,

but abandoned the demonstration of MCP.

Neither option preserved the intended architecture.

---

# 11.17 Docker Hypothesis

New hypothesis

The application is correct.

The runtime is incorrect.

Therefore,

instead of changing the application,

change the runtime.

Docker became the preferred solution.

---

# 11.18 Docker Validation

Docker image included

✓ Python

✓ Node

✓ npm

✓ npx

Local testing succeeded.

Render deployment succeeded.

Filesystem MCP started correctly.

Reports were generated.

The hypothesis was confirmed.

---

# 11.19 Major Engineering Lessons

Lesson 1

Working code can still fail because of environment differences.

---

Lesson 2

Every runtime dependency must be considered,

not only Python packages.

---

Lesson 3

Tool isolation dramatically reduces debugging complexity.

---

Lesson 4

Logs rarely identify the true root cause.

They reveal symptoms.

Engineering reasoning identifies causes.

---

Lesson 5

Docker is not merely a deployment tool.

It is an environment standardization tool.

---

# 11.20 What Was Actually Proven?

The project proved that

Google ADK

Gemini

Remote MCP

Local MCP

Docker

Render

can all work together successfully,

provided that every runtime dependency is satisfied.

The largest challenge was never the AI model.

It was understanding how different execution environments affected MCP servers built with different technologies.

---

# 11.21 Final Engineering Reflection

Looking back,

the project was never simply about deploying an AI application.

It became an exercise in understanding:

- AI orchestration
- Protocol design
- Runtime dependencies
- Cloud deployment
- Containerization
- Incremental debugging
- Systems thinking

Perhaps the most valuable outcome was not the final application itself,

but the engineering methodology developed during the journey.

That methodology—isolating variables, validating assumptions, and standardizing environments—is transferable to any future AI system built with Google ADK, MCP, or other agent frameworks.